  "query": "How do different partial harvesting methods in USA forests compare to clearcutting in their impact on salamander populations?",
  "relevant_summary": "Across North America, a meta-analysis found partial harvests (including shelterwood, group/individual-tree harvesting, and thinning) caused smaller reductions in salamander populations than clearcutting [851, 844, 852]. In the USA, shelterwood harvesting yielded salamander abundances that were higher, similar, or initially higher then similar compared to clearcutting [851]. Harvesting trees in small groups did not produce higher salamander abundance than clearcutting in three USA studies [844]. Thinning often resulted in higher amphibian abundance than clearcuts or a less negative overall response, with mixed effects by species and time since harvest; salamander use of thinned forest during emigration was significantly greater than clearcuts in one study [852].",
